@startuml
title Label Editor - High Level Interaction Flow

actor User

participant "UI: Dashboard" as Dashboard
participant "UI: Label Editor" as Editor
participant "Canvas Workspace" as Canvas
participant "Sidebar Layer Manager" as Sidebar

User -> Dashboard: Select "Create New Label"
Dashboard -> Editor: Open Editor View
Editor -> User: Prompt for Dimensions (Width & Height)
User -> Editor: Enter Dimensions & Confirm
Editor -> Canvas: Initialize Label Canvas
Editor -> Sidebar: Initialize Empty Element List

== Adding Elements ==
User -> Editor: Click Add Text, Add Image, or Add Variable (Text/Barcode/QR)
Editor -> Canvas: Render New Element on Canvas
Editor -> Sidebar: Append New Element to Layer List

== Interacting with Canvas Elements ==
User -> Canvas: Click Element (Text/Image)
Canvas -> Canvas: Mark Element as Selected
User -> Canvas: Click and Drag Element
Canvas -> Canvas: Update Element X/Y Coordinates

User -> Canvas: Resize Image Element
Canvas -> Canvas: Update Image Dimensions

User -> Editor: Modify Text Styles (Font, Size, Bold)
Editor -> Canvas: Update Text Element Rendering

== Managing Layers via Sidebar ==
User -> Sidebar: Drag & Drop Element to New Position in List
Sidebar -> Editor: Trigger Layer Order Update
Editor -> Canvas: Re-render Elements based on New Z-Index Order

== Saving and Loading ==
User -> Editor: Click "Save Label"
Editor -> Dashboard: Serialize Label Data (Dimensions, Elements, Layers)
Dashboard -> Dashboard: Store Data (Database/Local Storage)

User -> Dashboard: Select "Load Label"
Dashboard -> Editor: Open Editor with Saved Data
Editor -> Canvas: Restore Canvas & Render Elements
Editor -> Sidebar: Restore Element List

@enduml
